            "properties": [
                [
                    "name",
                    "Valid Accounts"
                ],
                [
                    "ttp",
                    [
                        [
                            "tactic",
                            "TA0001"
                        ],
                        [
                            "technique",
                            "T1078"
                        ]
                    ]
                ],
                [
                    "description",
                    "ALPHV/BlackCat affiliates heavily rely on valid credentials as the predominant initial access method — obtaining them via phishing, prior data breaches, credential-theft malware, or underground markets. Authenticating with legitimate accounts allows attackers to blend seamlessly into normal enterprise activity, evade detection, and maintain persistent access before escalating to domain-wide compromise and ransomware deployment."
                ],
                [
                    "confidence",
                    null
                ],
